19/04/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The small ethnic Albanian Party of Democratic Prosperity (PDP) has accepted Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski's recent invitation to join the multiethnic coalition government, PDP Chairman Abduladi Vejseli confirmed on Wednesday (April 18th). 
It would become the second ethnic Albanian partner of Gruevski's VMRO-DPMNE, after the Democratic Party of Albanians. 
(MRT, Vecer - 19/04/07)
